<BaseLayout title="About | Wampus Labs" description="Wampus Labs is a small Wisconsin technology company focused on useful solutions and plain-English help.">
  <section class="page-hero section"><div class="container narrow">
    <p class="eyebrow">About Wampus Labs</p><h1>Built for people who have work to do.</h1>
    <p>Wampus Labs is a small Wisconsin technology company with a pretty simple goal: make technology less of a hassle.</p>
  </div></section>
  <section class="section story-section"><div class="container two-column">
    <div><p class="eyebrow">Why this exists</p><h2>Good tech doesn’t need to show off.</h2></div>
    <div class="prose-large">
      <p>Too many businesses get stuck with tools that are confusing, unreliable, or much bigger than the problem they were meant to solve.</p>
      <p>Wampus Labs takes a different approach. Listen closely. Explain the options without the jargon. Build something sensible. Then stick around to make sure it keeps working.</p>
      <p>That might mean securing Microsoft 365, automating a slow approval process, running five digital signs on Raspberry Pis, or writing a small app that finally replaces a temperamental spreadsheet.</p>
    </div>
  </div></section>
  <section class="section principles-section"><div class="container">
    <div class="section-heading"><p class="eyebrow">How we work</p><h2>A few things you can expect.</h2></div>
    <div class="principle-grid">
      <article><span>01</span><h3>Plain answers</h3><p>You’ll know what we recommend, why, and what it costs.</p></article>
      <article><span>02</span><h3>Practical choices</h3><p>No oversized setup just because it looks impressive.</p></article>
      <article><span>03</span><h3>Security from the start</h3><p>It’s part of the plan, not an add-on after something goes wrong.</p></article>
      <article><span>04</span><h3>Room to grow</h3><p>Start small without painting yourself into a corner.</p></article>
    </div>
  </div></section>
</BaseLayout>
